q.enqueue(1)
q.enqueue(2)
q.enqueue(3)

print(q.dequeue())  # Output: 1
print(q.dequeue())  # Output: 2
print(q.dequeue())  # Output: 3
print(q.is_empty())  # Output: True
```

This implementation uses two stacks, `stack1` and `stack2`. The `enqueue` method adds items to `stack1`, and the `dequeue` method removes items from `stack2`. When `stack2` is empty, it moves all items from `stack1` to `stack2` before removing the top item. This ensures that the order of items is preserved, as required for a queue.
